In [69]:
#Dynamic plotting
from ipywidgets import interactive
def power(n):
    x = np.linspace(-5,5,10)
    y = x**n
    
    plt.figure(figsize = (7,7))
    plt.title(f'Power {n} polynomial')
    
    plt.plot(x,y,label = f'X to the power {n}')
    plt.axvline(0,c = 'black')
    
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel(f'X^{n}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True)
    
    return x,y
In [70]:
